<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="131" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                        <head>No. 121.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoffman</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-05-02"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 2,
                                1876</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Winslow applies for <hi rend="italic">habeas corpus</hi> to-morrow.
                            British government will oppose his immediate release. Shall not
                            intervene unless instructed. Papers asked for in House of Commons;
                            refused for the present.</p>
                        <closer><signed>HOFFMAN.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>